      <notes>
        <note appliesTo="source">line: 20</note>
      </notes>
      <segment state="initial">
        <source>You can configure add-on settings from NVDA menu/Preferences/Settings/Sound Splitter category.</source>
        <target>You can configure add-on settings from NVDA menu/Preferences/Settings/Sound Splitter category.</target>
      </segment>
    </unit>
    <unit id="931b08fb-dcb9-4d77-9e2c-0f5f7ddfacc5">
      <notes>
        <note appliesTo="source">line: 22</note>
        <note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
      </notes>
      <segment state="initial">
        <source>Split NVDA sound and applications' sounds into left and right channels: checking this checkbox will enable the sound splitting feature.</source>
        <target>Split NVDA sound and applications' sounds into left and right channels: checking this checkbox will enable the sound splitting feature.</target>
      </segment>
    </unit>
    <unit id="b529eeb2-bf42-4938-8c96-363b0b784a23">
      <notes>
        <note appliesTo="source">line: 23</note>
        <note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
      </notes>
      <segment state="initial">
        <source>Switch left and right during sound split: by default, NVDA will be heard through the right channel if sound splitting is on. You can instead hear NVDA through the left channel by checking this checkbox.</source>
        <target>Switch left and right during sound split: by default, NVDA will be heard through the right channel if sound splitting is on. You can instead hear NVDA through the left channel by checking this checkbox.</target>
      </segment>
    </unit>
